naji. Entry free; small fee for lighthouse (\u20b920). Great photo ops. |\\n| **10:30 \u2013 12:00** | **Sinquerim Beach** | Walk along the sand, optional short dip. |\\n| **12:00 \u2013 13:30** | **Lunch at Fisherman\u2019s Wharf (Cavelossim)** | Seafood thali, river\u2011view. Approx. \u20b9350\u2011\u20b9500 per person. |\\n| **13:30 \u2013 14:30** | **Return to hotel \u2013 check\u2011in / freshen up** | |\\n| **14:30 \u2013 16:00** | **Explore Panaji Old\u2011Town (Latin Quarter \u2013 Fontainhas)** | Stroll the pastel\u2011coloured lanes, visit *Our Lady of the Immaculate Conception* church, browse art\u2011gallery shops. |\\n| **16:00 \u2013 17:30** | **Miramar Beach** | Sunset walk; optional camel ride (\u20b9300). |\\n| **18:00 \u2013 20:00** | **Dinner at Mum\u2019s Kitchen (Panaji)** | Authentic Goan cuisine (fish curry, xacuti). Approx. \u20b9600\u2011\u20b9800. |\\n| **20:30 \u2013 22:30** | **Nightlife \u2013 \u201cClub Cabana\u201d (Arpora) or \u201cTito\u2019s\u201d (Baga)** | Taxi/auto (\u2248\u20b9250 each way). Entry free; drinks \u20b9250\u2011\u20b9400 each. |\\n| **22:30** | **Return to hotel** | Rest for Day\u202f2. |\\n\\n**Travel tip:** Keep a **scooter** (\u20b9350\u2011\u20b9450 per day) for the whole trip \u2013 it\u2019s the cheapest way to hop between beaches and attractions.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### DAY\u202f2 \u2013 \u201cSouth Goa Serenity & Culture\u201d\\n\\n| Time | Activity | Details & Approx. Duration |\\n|------|----------|----------------------------|\\n| **07:30 \u2013 08:30** | **Early Breakfast** | Light breakfast at hotel or a local bakery (e.g., *Baker\u2019s Corner*). |\\n| **08:30 \u2013 10:00** | **Drive to Old Goa (\u22481\u202fhr)** | Hire a driver or self\u2011drive scooter. |\\n| **10:00 \u2013 12:00** | **Basilica of Bom\u202fJesus & Se Cathedral** | UNESCO sites. Entry free; donation optional. |\\n| **12:00 \u2013 13:30** | **Lunch at *Martin\u2019s Corner* (Betalbatim)** | Famous for prawn balch\u00e3o. Approx. \u20b9500\u2011\u20b9700. |\\n| **13:30 \u2013 15:00** | **Colva Beach \u2013 Relax / Swim** | Optional water\u2011sport: parasailing (\u20b91,200) or jet\u2011ski (\u20b91,500). |\\n| **15:00 \u2013 16:30** | **Caf\u00e9 stop at *Cafe Chocolatti* (Palolem)** | Ice\u2011cream, coffee, Instagram\u2011worthy desserts. |\\n| **16:30 \u2013 18:00** | **Explore Palolem (or Agonda) Beach** | Sunset at Palolem is spectacular; gentle waves, hammocks. |\\n| **18:30 \u2013 20:00** | **Dinner at *Art Resort* (Palolem)** | Beachfront, Goan\u2011fusion menu. Approx. \u20b9800\u2011\u20b91,200. |\\n| **20:30 \u2013 22:00** | **Optional: Night Market (Arpora) \u2013 only on Saturdays** | If your trip falls on a Saturday, take a quick auto to the market for souvenirs, street food, live music. |\\n| **22:30** | **Return to hotel (or head to airport/train station)** | If you have a night departure, arrange a taxi in advance (\u2248\u20b91,200). |\\n\\n**Alternative for Day\u202f2 (if you prefer more beach time):** Skip Old Goa and spend the whole day at **Benaulim** & **Cavelossim** beaches, with a sunset cruise on the **Mandovi River** (\u20b92,500 per person, includes dinner & music).\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 4\ufe0f\u20e3 DETAILED BUDGET CALCULATOR (Mid\u2011Range Example)\\n\\n| Category | Cost (INR) | Notes |\\n|----------|------------|-------|\\n| **Accommodation** (1 night, double occupancy) | \u20b94,200 | The Crown Goa \u2013 comfortable 3\u2011star with pool. |\\n| **Food & Drinks** (2 days) | \u20b92,800 | Breakfast (included), lunch & dinner at mid\u2011range restaurants, occasional coffee/juice. |\\n| **Transport** | \u20b91,500 | Scooter rent (\u20b9450 \u00d72) + fuel (\u20b9300) + occasional auto/taxi for night\u2011life (\u20b9250 \u00d72). |\\n| **Attraction Fees** | \u20b9800 | Fort Aguada lighthouse, water\u2011sport (parasailing), entry to churches (donations). |\\n| **Miscellaneous** | \u20b9700 | Souvenirs, tips, Wi\u2011Fi, bottled water. |\\n| **Total per person** | **\u2248\u202f\u20b99,800** | Well under \u20b950,000 \u2013 you could upgrade any line item or add a spa treatment. |\\n\\n*If you travel with a companion sharing the same room, the **per\u2011person** cost halves for accommodation, bringing the total to ~\u20b97,500 each.*\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 5\ufe0f\u20e3 PRACTICAL TRAVEL TIPS\\n\\n| Topic | Recommendation |\\n|-------|----------------|\\n| **Best time to visit** | **Oct\u202f\u2013\u202fFeb** (cool, dry). Monsoon (Jun\u2011Sept) offers lush scenery & lower rates but limited beach activities. |\\n| **Getting there** | Goa International Airport (Dabolim) \u2013 30\u202fmin by taxi to Panaji. Alternatively, Konkan Railway (Madgaon) if you\u2019re coming from Mumbai/Delhi. |\\n| **Local transport** | Rent a **scooter** (\u20b9350\u2011\u20b9450/day). Carry a **helmet** (mandatory). For longer distances, use **Ola/Uber** or pre\u2011book a **private car**. |\\n| **Currency** | ATMs are plentiful in Panaji, Calangute, and Margao. Keep some cash for beach shacks that don\u2019t accept cards. |\\n| **Safety** | Goa is tourist\u2011friendly. Keep an eye on belongings on crowded beaches, especially at night. Drink responsibly; many beach bars have a \u201cno\u2011outside\u2011alcohol\u201d rule. |\\n| **Health** | Stay hydrated, use sunscreen (SPF\u202f30+). Carry basic meds (pain reliever, anti\u2011diarrheal). |\\n| **Cultural etiquette** | Dress modestly when visiting churches and temples. Remove shoes before entering religious sites. |\\n| **Connectivity** | Free Wi\u2011Fi at most hotels and caf\u00e9s. For mobile data, buy a **Jio/Idea prepaid SIM** (\u20b9199 for 2\u202fGB + 28\u202fdays). |\\n| **Packing list** | Light cotton clothing, swimwear, flip\u2011flops, comfortable walking shoes, hat, sunglasses, reusable water bottle, small day\u2011backpack. |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 6\ufe0f\u20e3 QUICK CHECKLIST BEFORE YOU GO\\n\\n- [ ] Book hotel (choose budget/mid\u2011range/luxury) \u2013 confirm check\u2011in time.  \\n- [ ] Reserve a **scooter** online (many platforms allow advance booking).  \\n- [ ] Pre\u2011pay airport\u2011to\u2011hotel transfer (\u20b9800\u2011\u20b91,200) if arriving late at night.  \\n- [ ] Print or screenshot e\u2011tickets for any water\u2011sport activity you want to pre\u2011book.  \\n- [ ] Pack a small **first\u2011aid kit** (band\u2011aids, antiseptic wipes).  \\n- [ ] Download **Goa Tourism app** for offline maps and event updates.  \\n\\n---\\n\\n### \ud83c\udf89 Your 2\u2011Day Goa adventure is ready!  \\n\\nPick the accommodation tier that feels right, follow the itinerary, and you\u2019ll experience the best of Goa\u2019s beaches, heritage, and nightlife\u2014all comfortably within your **\u20b950,000** budget. Have a fantastic trip! \ud83c\udf34\ud83c\udfd6\ufe0f\ud83d\udea4\",\"type\":\"TextMessage\"}}", "sender": "Travel_Planner_9dad0395-0f59-4232-a2bf-58ca92087960/9dad0395-0f59-4232-a2bf-58ca92087960", "receiver": "output_topic_9dad0395-0f59-4232-a2bf-58ca92087960/9dad0395-0f59-4232-a2bf-58ca92087960", "kind": "MessageKind.PUBLISH", "delivery_stage": "DeliveryStage.SEND", "type": "Message"}
2026-02-20 07:02:44 - INFO - 405 -Publishing message of type GroupChatAgentResponse to all subscribers: {'response': Response(chat_message=TextMessage(id='ded269a9-8f96-4cc4-a10a-58894e5f1fcb', source='Travel_Planner', models_usage=RequestUsage(prompt_tokens=272, completion_tokens=2828), metadata={}, created_at=datetime.datetime(2026, 2, 20, 1, 32, 44, 1845, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), content='## 2\u2011Day Goa Getaway – INR\u202f50,000 (\u2248\u202f$600)  \n**Travel style:** Relaxed, beach\u2011centric with a dash of culture & nightlife.  \n**Base city:** Panaji (the state capital) – centrally located, good bus/auto hub and easy to reach the north\u2011 and south\u2011coast attractions.  \n\n---\n\n### 1\ufe0f\u20e3 QUICK BUDGET BREAKDOWN (All figures in INR)\n\n| Item | Budget\u2011Friendly (\u20b9) | Mid\u2011Range (\u20b9) | Luxury (\u20b9) |\n|------|--------------------|--------------|-----------|\n| **Accommodation** (1 night) | \u20b91,200 – 1,800 (guesthouse/hostel) | \u20b93,500 – 5,500 (3\u2011star hotel) | \u20b99,000 – 12,000 (4\u20115\u2605 resort) |\n| **Food & Drinks** (2 days) | \u20b91,200 – 1,500 (street eats, local cafés) | \u20b92,500 – 3,500 (mid\u2011range restaurants) | \u20b95,000 – 7,000 (sea\u2011view dining, cocktails) |\n| **Local Transport** | \u20b9800 – 1,200 (scooter rent + occasional auto) | \u20b91,200 – 1,800 (scooter + occasional taxi) | \u20b92,500 – 3,500 (private car with driver) |\n| **Attraction Fees** | \u20b9300 – 600 (entry to forts, museums) | \u20b9600 – 1,200 (water\u2011sports, entry to heritage sites) | \u20b91,200 – 2,000 (guided tours, premium water\u2011sports) |\n| **Miscellaneous** (souvenirs, tips, Wi\u2011Fi) | \u20b9500 – 800 | \u20b9800 – 1,200 | \u20b91,200 – 1,800 |\n| **Total (per person)** | **\u2248\u202f\u20b95,000** | **\u2248\u202f\u20b913,000** | **\u2248\u202f\u20b926,000** |\n\n> **Even the luxury option stays well under your \u20b950,000 ceiling**, leaving plenty of room for extra splurges (e.g., sunset cruise, spa, or a night out at a beach club).\n\n---\n\n## 2\ufe0f\u20e3 HOTEL RECOMMENDATIONS  \n\n| Category | Property (Panaji) | Approx. Nightly Rate* | Highlights |\n|----------|-------------------|----------------------|------------|\n| **Budget** | **Zostel Goa – Panaji** (hostel\u2011style dorms & private rooms) | \u20b91,200 – 1,800 | Central location, rooftop lounge, free Wi\u2011Fi, social vibe. |\n| | **Casa De Goa** (heritage guesthouse) | \u20b91,500 – 2,200 | Portuguese\u2011style décor, garden, close to Miramar Beach. |\n| **Mid\u2011Range** | **The Crown Goa – Panaji** | \u20b93,500 – 4,500 | 3\u2011star, rooftop pool, complimentary breakfast, near the river. |\n| | **Novotel Goa Resort & Spa** (Cavelossim) – a little south but worth the 30\u2011min drive | \u20b95,000 – 5,500 | Beachfront, spa, multiple dining options. |\n| **Luxury** | **Taj Exotica Resort & Spa** (Benaulim) | \u20b99,000 – 12,000 | 5\u2011star beachfront, infinity pool, world\u2011class service. |\n| | **Alila Diwa Goa** (Majorda) | \u20b910,000 – 13,000 | Lush rice\u2011paddy setting, private beach access, excellent spa. |\n\n\\*Rates are for **one night** (double occupancy). Prices fluctuate with season; off\u2011peak (June\u2011Sept) is cheaper.\n\n---\n\n## 3\ufe0f\u20e3 DETAILED 2\u2011DAY ITINERARY  \n\n> **Assumption:** Arrival in Goa by flight/train the evening before Day\u202f1, or early morning on Day\u202f1. Check\u2011in time is 2\u202fpm (most hotels). Adjust morning activities accordingly.\n\n### DAY\u202f1 – “North Goa Highlights & Sunset”\n\n| Time | Activity | Details & Approx. Duration |\n|------|----------|----------------------------|\n| **08:00 – 09:00** | **Breakfast** | Hotel buffet (mid\u2011range) or local café: try *Goan poee* with *chorizo* or *prawn rava toast*. |\n| **09:00 – 10:30** | **Fort Aguada & Lighthouse** | 20\u202fmin drive from Panaji. Entry free; small fee for lighthouse (\u20b920). Great photo ops. |\n| **10:30 – 12:00** | **Sinquerim Beach** | Walk along the sand, optional short dip. |\n| **12:00 – 13:30** | **Lunch at Fisherman’s Wharf (Cavelossim)** | Seafood thali, river\u2011view. Approx. \u20b9350\u2011\u20b9500 per person. |\n| **13:30 – 14:30** | **Return to hotel – check\u2011in / freshen up** | |\n| **14:30 – 16:00** | **Explore Panaji Old\u2011Town (Latin Quarter – Fontainhas)** | Stroll the pastel\u2011coloured lanes, visit *Our Lady of the Immaculate Conception* church, browse art\u2011gallery shops. |\n| **16:00 – 17:30** | **Miramar Beach** | Sunset walk; optional camel ride (\u20b9300). |\n| **18:00 – 20:00** | **Dinner at Mum’s Kitchen (Panaji)** | Authentic Goan cuisine (fish curry, xacuti). Approx. \u20b9600\u2011\u20b9800. |\n| **20:30 – 22:30** | **Nightlife – “Club Cabana” (Arpora) or “Tito’s” (Baga)** | Taxi/auto (\u2248\u20b9250 each way). Entry free; drinks \u20b9250\u2011\u20b9400 each. |\n| **22:30** | **Return to hotel** | Rest for Day\u202f2. |\n\n**Travel tip:** Keep a **scooter** (\u20b9350\u2011\u20b9450 per day) for the whole trip – it’s the cheapest way to hop between beaches and attractions.\n\n---\n\n### DAY\u202f2 – “South Goa Serenity & Culture”\n\n| Time | Activity | Details & Approx. Duration |\n|------|----------|----------------------------|\n| **07:30 – 08:30** | **Early Breakfast** | Light breakfast at hotel or a local bakery (e.g., *Baker’s Corner*). |\n| **08:30 – 10:00** | **Drive to Old Goa (\u22481\u202fhr)** | Hire a driver or self\u2011drive scooter. |\n| **10:00 – 12:00** | **Basilica of Bom\u202fJesus & Se Cathedral** | UNESCO sites. Entry free; donation optional. |\n| **12:00 – 13:30** | **Lunch at *Martin’s Corner* (Betalbatim)** | Famous for prawn balchăo. Approx. \u20b9500\u2011\u20b9700. |\n| **13:30 – 15:00** | **Colva Beach – Relax / Swim** | Optional water\u2011sport: parasailing (\u20b91,200) or jet\u2011ski (\u20b91,500). |\n| **15:00 – 16:30** | **Café stop at *Cafe Chocolatti* (Palolem)** | Ice\u2011cream, coffee, Instagram\u2011worthy desserts. |\n| **16:30 – 18:00** | **Explore Palolem (or Agonda) Beach** | Sunset at Palolem is spectacular; gentle waves, hammocks. |\n| **18:30 – 20:00** | **Dinner at *Art Resort* (Palolem)** | Beachfront, Goan\u2011fusion menu. Approx. \u20b9800\u2011\u20b91,200. |\n| **20:30 – 22:00** | **Optional: Night Market (Arpora) – only on Saturdays** | If your trip falls on a Saturday, take a quick auto to the market for souvenirs, street food, live music. |\n| **22:30** | **Return to hotel (or head to airport/train station)** | If you have a night departure, arrange a taxi in advance (\u2248\u20b91,200). |\n\n**Alternative for Day\u202f2 (if you prefer more beach time):** Skip Old Goa and spend the whole day at **Benaulim** & **Cavelossim** beaches, with a sunset cruise on the **Mandovi River** (\u20b92,500 per person, includes dinner & music).\n\n---\n\n## 4\ufe0f\u20e3 DETAILED BUDGET CALCULATOR (Mid\u2011Range Example)\n\n| Category | Cost (INR) | Notes |\n|----------|------------|-------|\n| **Accommodation** (1 night, double occupancy) | \u20b94,200 | The Crown Goa – comfortable 3\u2011star with pool. |\n| **Food & Drinks** (2 days) | \u20b92,800 | Breakfast (included), lunch & dinner at mid\u2011range restaurants, occasional coffee/juice. |\n| **Transport** | \u20b91,500 | Scooter rent (\u20b9450 ×2) + fuel (\u20b9300) + occasional auto/taxi for night\u2011life (\u20b9250 ×2). |\n| **Attraction Fees** | \u20b9800 | Fort Aguada lighthouse, water\u2011sport (parasailing), entry to churches (donations). |\n| **Miscellaneous** | \u20b9700 | Souvenirs, tips, Wi\u2011Fi, bottled water. |\n| **Total per person** | **\u2248\u202f\u20b99,800** | Well under \u20b950,000 – you could upgrade any line item or add a spa treatment. |\n\n*If you travel with a companion sharing the same room, the **per\u2011person** cost halves for accommodation, bringing the total to ~\u20b97,500 each.*\n\n---\n\n## 5\ufe0f\u20e3 PRACTICAL TRAVEL TIPS\n\n| Topic | Recommendation |\n|-------|----------------|\n| **Best time to visit** | **Oct\u202f–\u202fFeb** (cool, dry). Monsoon (Jun\u2011Sept) offers lush scenery & lower rates but limited beach activities. |\n| **Getting there** | Goa International Airport (Dabolim) – 30\u202fmin by taxi to Panaji. Alternatively, Konkan Railway (Madgaon) if you’re coming from Mumbai/Delhi. |\n| **Local transport** | Rent a **scooter** (\u20b9350\u2011\u20b9450/day). Carry a **helmet** (mandatory). For longer distances, use **Ola/Uber** or pre\u2011book a **private car**. |\n| **Currency** | ATMs are plentiful in Panaji, Calangute, and Margao. Keep some cash for beach shacks that don’t accept cards. |\n| **Safety** | Goa is tourist\u2011friendly. Keep an eye on belongings on crowded beaches, especially at night. Drink responsibly; many beach bars have a “no\u2011outside\u2011alcohol” rule. |\n| **Health** | Stay hydrated, use sunscreen (SPF\u202f30+). Carry basic meds (pain reliever, anti\u2011diarrheal). |\n| **Cultural etiquette** | Dress modestly when visiting churches and temples. Remove shoes before entering religious sites. |\n| **Connectivity** | Free Wi\u2011Fi at most hotels and cafés. For mobile data, buy a **Jio/Idea prepaid SIM** (\u20b9199 for 2\u202fGB + 28\u202fdays). |\n| **Packing list** | Light cotton clothing, swimwear, flip\u2011flops, comfortable walking shoes, hat, sunglasses, reusable water bottle, small day\u2011backpack. |\n\n---\n\n## 6\ufe0f\u20e3 QUICK CHECKLIST BEFORE YOU GO\n\n- [ ] Book hotel (choose budget/mid\u2011range/luxury) – confirm check\u2011in time.  \n- [ ] Reserve a **scooter** online (many platforms allow advance booking).  \n- [ ] Pre\u2011pay airport\u2011to\u2011hotel transfer (\u20b9800\u2011\u20b91,200) if arriving late at night.  \n- [ ] Print or screenshot e\u2011tickets for any water\u2011sport activity you want to pre\u2011book.  \n- [ ] Pack a small **first\u2011aid kit** (band\u2011aids, antiseptic wipes).  \n- [ ] Download **Goa Tourism app** for offline maps and event updates.  \n\n---\n\n### \U0001f389 Your 2\u2011Day Goa adventure is ready!  \n\nPick the accommodation tier that feels right, follow the itinerary, and you’ll experience the best of Goa’s beaches, heritage, and nightlife—all comfortably within your **\u20b950,000** budget. Have a fantastic trip! \U0001f334\U0001f3d6\ufe0f\U0001f6a4', type='TextMessage'), inner_messages=[]), 'name': 'Travel_Planner'}
2026-02-20 07:02:44 - INFO - 410 -{"payload": "{\"response\":{\"chat_message\":{\"id\":\"ded269a9-8f96-4cc4-a10a-58894e5f1fcb\",\"source\":\"Travel_Planner\",\"models_usage\":{\"prompt_tokens\":272,\"completion_tokens\":2828},\"metadata\":{},\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T01:32:44.001845Z\",\"content\":\"## 2\u2011Day Goa Getaway \u2013 INR\u202f50,000 (\u2248\u202f$600)  \\n**Travel style:** Relaxed, beach\u2011centric with a dash of culture & nightlife.  \\n**Base city:** Panaji (the state capital) \u2013 centrally located, good bus/auto hub and easy to reach the north\u2011 and south\u2011coast attractions.  \\n\\n---\\n\\n### 1\ufe0f\u20e3 QUICK BUDGET BREAKDOWN (All figures in INR)\\n\\n| Item | Budget\u2011Friendly (\u20b9) | Mid\u2011Range (\u20b9) | Luxury (\u20b9) |\\n|------|--------------------|--------------|-----------|\\n| **Accommodation** (1 night) | \u20b91,200 \u2013 1,800 (guesthouse/hostel) | \u20b93,500 \u2013 5,500 (3\u2011star hotel) | \u20b99,000 \u2013 12,000 (4\u20115\u2605 resort) |\\n| **Food & Drinks** (2 days) | \u20b91,200 \u2013 1,500 (street eats, local caf\u00e9s) | \u20b92,500 \u2013 3,500 (mid\u2011range restaurants) | \u20b95,000 \u2013 7,000 (sea\u2011view dining, cocktails) |\\n| **Local Transport** | \u20b9800 \u2013 1,200 (scooter rent + occasional auto) | \u20b91,200 \u2013 1,800 (scooter + occasional taxi) | \u20b92,500 \u2013 3,500 (private car with driver) |\\n| **Attraction Fees** | \u20b9300 \u2013 600 (entry to forts, museums) | \u20b9600 \u2013 1,200 (water\u2011sports, entry to heritage sites) | \u20b91,200 \u2013 2,000 (guided tours, premium water\u2011sports) |\\n| **Miscellaneous** (souvenirs, tips, Wi\u2011Fi) | \u20b9500 \u2013 800 | \u20b9800 \u2013 1,200 | \u20b91,200 \u2013 1,800 |\\n| **Total (per person)** | **\u2248\u202f\u20b95,000** | **\u2248\u202f\u20b913,000** | **\u2248\u202f\u20b926,000** |\\n\\n> **Even the luxury option stays well under your \u20b950,000 ceiling**, leaving plenty of room for extra splurges (e.g., sunset cruise, spa, or a night out at a beach club).\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 2\ufe0f\u20e3 HOTEL RECOMMENDATIONS  \\n\\n| Category | Property (Panaji) | Approx. Nightly Rate* | Highlights |\\n|----------|-------------------|----------------------|------------|\\n| **Budget** | **Zostel Goa \u2013 Panaji** (hostel\u2011style dorms & private rooms) | \u20b91,200 \u2013 1,800 | Central location, rooftop lounge, free Wi\u2011Fi, social vibe. |\\n| | **Casa De Goa** (heritage guesthouse) | \u20b91,500 \u2013 2,200 | Portuguese\u2011style d\u00e9cor, garden, close to Miramar Beach. |\\n| **Mid\u2011Range** | **The Crown Goa \u2013 Panaji** | \u20b93,500 \u2013 4,500 | 3\u2011star, rooftop pool, complimentary breakfast, near the river. |\\n| | **Novotel Goa Resort & Spa** (Cavelossim) \u2013 a little south but worth the 30\u2011min drive | \u20b95,000 \u2013 5,500 | Beachfront, spa, multiple dining options. |\\n| **Luxury** | **Taj Exotica Resort & Spa** (Benaulim) | \u20b99,000 \u2013 12,000 | 5\u2011star beachfront, infinity pool, world\u2011class service. |\\n| | **Alila Diwa Goa** (Majorda) | \u20b910,000 \u2013 13,000 | Lush rice\u2011paddy setting, private beach access, excellent spa. |\\n\\n\\\\*Rates are for **one night** (double occupancy). Prices fluctuate with season; off\u2011peak (June\u2011Sept) is cheaper.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 3\ufe0f\u20e3 DETAILED 2\u2011DAY ITINERARY  \\n\\n> **Assumption:** Arrival in Goa by flight/train the evening before Day\u202f1, or early morning on Day\u202f1. Check\u2011in time is 2\u202fpm (most hotels). Adjust morning activities accordingly.\\n\\n### DAY\u202f1 \u2013 \u201cNorth Goa Highlights & Sunset\u201d\\n\\n| Time | Activity | Details & Approx. Duration |\\n|------|----------|----------------------------|\\n| **08:00 \u2013 09:00** | **Breakfast** | Hotel buffet (mid\u2011range) or local caf\u00e9: try *Goan poee* with *chorizo* or *prawn rava toast*. |\\n| **09:00 \u2013 10:30** | **Fort Aguada & Lighthouse** | 20\u202fmin drive from Panaji. Entry free; small fee for lighthouse (\u20b920). Great photo ops. |\\n| **10:30 \u2013 12:00** | **Sinquerim Beach** | Walk along the sand, optional short dip. |\\n| **12:00 \u2013 13:30** | **Lunch at Fisherman\u2019s Wharf (Cavelossim)** | Seafood thali, river\u2011view. Approx. \u20b9350\u2011\u20b9500 per person. |\\n| **13:30 \u2013 14:30** | **Return to hotel \u2013 check\u2011in / freshen up** | |\\n| **14:30 \u2013 16:00** | **Explore Panaji Old\u2011Town (Latin Quarter \u2013 Fontainhas)** | Stroll the pastel\u2011coloured lanes, visit *Our Lady of the Immaculate Conception* church, browse art\u2011gallery shops. |\\n| **16:00 \u2013 17:30** | **Miramar Beach** | Sunset walk; optional camel ride (\u20b9300). |\\n| **18:00 \u2013 20:00** | **Dinner at Mum\u2019s Kitchen (Panaji)** | Authentic Goan cuisine (fish curry, xacuti). Approx. \u20b9600\u2011\u20b9800. |\\n| **20:30 \u2013 22:30** | **Nightlife \u2013 \u201cClub Cabana\u201d (Arpora) or \u201cTito\u2019s\u201d (Baga)** | Taxi/auto (\u2248\u20b9250 each way). Entry free; drinks \u20b9250\u2011\u20b9400 each. |\\n| **22:30** | **Return to hotel** | Rest for Day\u202f2. |\\n\\n**Travel tip:** Keep a **scooter** (\u20b9350\u2011\u20b9450 per day) for the whole trip \u2013 it\u2019s the cheapest way to hop between beaches and attractions.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### DAY\u202f2 \u2013 \u201cSouth Goa Serenity & Culture\u201d\\n\\n| Time | Activity | Details & Approx. Duration |\\n|------|----------|----------------------------|\\n| **07:30 \u2013 08:30** | **Early Breakfast** | Light breakfast at hotel or a local bakery (e.g., *Baker\u2019s Corner*). |\\n| **08:30 \u2013 10:00** | **Drive to Old Goa (\u22481\u202fhr)** | Hire a driver or self\u2011drive scooter. |\\n| **10:00 \u2013 12:00** | **Basilica of Bom\u202fJesus & Se Cathedral** | UNESCO sites. Entry free; donation optional. |\\n| **12:00 \u2013 13:30** | **Lunch at *Martin\u2019s Corner* (Betalbatim)** | Famous for prawn balch\u00e3o. Approx. \u20b9500\u2011\u20b9700. |\\n| **13:30 \u2013 15:00** | **Colva Beach \u2013 Relax / Swim** | Optional water\u2011sport: parasailing (\u20b91,200) or jet\u2011ski (\u20b91,500). |\\n| **15:00 \u2013 16:30** | **Caf\u00e9 stop at *Cafe Chocolatti* (Palolem)** | Ice\u2011cream, coffee, Instagram\u2011worthy desserts. |\\n| **16:30 \u2013 18:00** | **Explore Palolem (or Agonda) Beach** | Sunset at Palolem is spectacular; gentle waves, hammocks. |\\n| **18:30 \u2013 20:00** | **Dinner at *Art Resort* (Palolem)** | Beachfront, Goan\u2011fusion menu. Approx. \u20b9800\u2011\u20b91,200. |\\n| **20:30 \u2013 22:00** | **Optional: Night Market (Arpora) \u2013 only on Saturdays** | If your trip falls on a Saturday, take a quick auto to the market for souvenirs, street food, live music. |\\n| **22:30** | **Return to hotel (or head to airport/train station)** | If you have a night departure, arrange a taxi in advance (\u2248\u20b91,200). |\\n\\n**Alternative for Day\u202f2 (if you prefer more beach time):** Skip Old Goa and spend the whole day at **Benaulim** & **Cavelossim** beaches, with a sunset cruise on the **Mandovi River** (\u20b92,500 per person, includes dinner & music).\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 4\ufe0f\u20e3 DETAILED BUDGET CALCULATOR (Mid\u2011Range Example)\\n\\n| Category | Cost (INR) | Notes |\\n|----------|------------|-------|\\n| **Accommodation** (1 night, double occupancy) | \u20b94,200 | The Crown Goa \u2013 comfortable 3\u2011star with pool. |\\n| **Food & Drinks** (2 days) | \u20b92,800 | Breakfast (included), lunch & dinner at mid\u2011range restaurants, occasional coffee/juice. |\\n| **Transport** | \u20b91,500 | Scooter rent (\u20b9450 \u00d72) + fuel (\u20b9300) + occasional auto/taxi for night\u2011life (\u20b9250 \u00d72). |\\n| **Attraction Fees** | \u20b9800 | Fort Aguada lighthouse, water\u2011sport (parasailing), entry to churches (donations). |\\n| **Miscellaneous** | \u20b9700 | Souvenirs, tips, Wi\u2011Fi, bottled water. |\\n| **Total per person** | **\u2248\u202f\u20b99,800** | Well under \u20b950,000 \u2013 you could upgrade any line item or add a spa treatment. |\\n\\n*If you travel with a companion sharing the same room, the **per\u2011person** cost halves for accommodation, bringing the total to ~\u20b97,500 each.*\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 5\ufe0f\u20e3 PRACTICAL TRAVEL TIPS\\n\\n| Topic | Recommendation |\\n|-------|----------------|\\n| **Best time to visit** | **Oct\u202f\u2013\u202fFeb** (cool, dry). Monsoon (Jun\u2011Sept) offers lush scenery & lower rates but limited beach activities. |\\n| **Getting there** | Goa International Airport (Dabolim) \u2013 30\u202fmin by taxi to Panaji. Alternatively, Konkan Railway (Madgaon) if you\u2019re coming from Mumbai/Delhi. |\\n| **Local transport** | Rent a **scooter** (\u20b9350\u2011\u20b9450/day). Carry a **helmet** (mandatory). For longer distances, use **Ola/Uber** or pre\u2011book a **private car**. |\\n| **Currency** | ATMs are plentiful in Panaji, Calangute, and Margao. Keep some cash for beach shacks that don\u2019t accept cards. |\\n| **Safety** | Goa is tourist\u2011friendly. Keep an eye on belongings on crowded beaches, especially at night. Drink responsibly; many beach bars have a \u201cno\u2011outside\u2011alcohol\u201d rule. |\\n| **Health** | Stay hydrated, use sunscreen (SPF\u202f30+). Carry basic meds (pain reliever, anti\u2011diarrheal). |\\n| **Cultural etiquette** | Dress modestly when visiting churches and temples. Remove shoes before entering religious sites. |\\n| **Connectivity** | Free Wi\u2011Fi at most hotels and caf\u00e9s. For mobile data, buy a **Jio/Idea prepaid SIM** (\u20b9199 for 2\u202fGB + 28\u202fdays). |\\n| **Packing list** | Light cotton clothing, swimwear, flip\u2011flops, comfortable walking shoes, hat, sunglasses, reusable water bottle, small day\u2011backpack. |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 6\ufe0f\u20e3 QUICK CHECKLIST BEFORE YOU GO\\n\\n- [ ] Book hotel (choose budget/mid\u2011range/luxury) \u2013 confirm check\u2011in time.  \\n- [ ] Reserve a **scooter** online (many platforms allow advance booking).  \\n- [ ] Pre\u2011pay airport\u2011to\u2011hotel transfer (\u20b9800\u2011\u20b91,200) if arriving late at night.  \\n- [ ] Print or screenshot e\u2011tickets for any water\u2011sport activity you want to pre\u2011book.  \\n- [ ] Pack a small **first\u2011aid kit** (band\u2011aids, antiseptic wipes).  \\n- [ ] Download **Goa Tourism app** for offline maps and event updates.  \\n\\n---\\n\\n### \ud83c\udf89 Your 2\u2011Day Goa adventure is ready!  \\n\\nPick the accommodation tier that feels right, follow the itinerary, and you\u2019ll experience the best of Goa\u2019s beaches, heritage, and nightlife\u2014all comfortably within your **\u20b950,000** budget. Have a fantastic trip! \ud83c\udf34\ud83c\udfd6\ufe0f\ud83d\udea4\",\"type\":\"TextMessage\"},\"inner_messages\":[]},\"name\":\"Travel_Planner\"}", "sender": "Travel_Planner_9dad0395-0f59-4232-a2bf-58ca92087960/9dad0395-0f59-4232-a2bf-58ca92087960", "receiver": "group_topic_9dad0395-0f59-4232-a2bf-58ca92087960/9dad0395-0f59-4232-a2bf-58ca92087960", "kind": "MessageKind.PUBLISH", "delivery_stage": "DeliveryStage.SEND", "type": "Message"}
